organization.description: The Federal Laboratory Consortium for Technology Transfer (FLC) is the nationwide network of federal laboratories that provides the forum to develop strategies and opportunities for linking laboratory mission technologies and expertise with the marketplace.
organization.title: Federal Laboratory Consortium
organization.name: federal-laboratory-consortium

extras.value: Capabilities:   Multi-purpose test complex including DOD&#39;s premiere Fire Safety Test Enclosure (FSTE) and fire survivability test ranges    Capabilities to support the full spectrum of fire testing from laboratory to full scale (for the web version need to update FPT full-spectrum video clip)    Complete testing capabilities to determine effects of simulated and actual ballistic threats upon combat vehicle crew survivability    Ability to test and compare performance of fire extinguishing agents in a wide-range of applications and operational scenarios (combat vehicle engine compartments and crew compartments; hand-held fire extinguishers, ship structures; buildings, automotive systems, aviation, etc.)    Ability to determine critical fire extinguishing agent performance parameters such as:  - Fire out time  - Resultant chemical speciation and concentrations  - Thermal effects on crew and equipment    Asset fire protection available at test sites    Test sites support direct-fire engagement of hard and soft targets by gun and missile threats; mine attach; air burst and static firing; vehicle fire suppression; ammunition compartment testing; arena testing; rocket sled and compressed air gun or launching threats available    Comprehensive insensitive munitions testing capability (MIL-STD=2105B)  - Fast Cook-Off  - Slow Cook-Off  - Bullet Impact  - Fragmentation Impact  - Sympathetic Detonation    Multi-purpose test sites adaptable for environmental technology demonstration
